{{refimprove|date=July 2017}}
The '''International Association of Medical Translators and Writers and Related Sciences''' ({{lang-es|'''Asociación Internacional de Traductores y Redactores de Medicina y Ciencias Afines'''}}, [[acronym]] '''Tremédica''') is an international organization devoted to the promotion of the professions related to [[medical translation]].<ref name="about">[http://www.tremedica.org/info_general.html About TREMEDICA] {{es icon}}</ref>

Established in December 2005 in [[Washington, D.C.]] as a [[non-profit organization]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexis.pro/news/global/what-the-doctor-said/ |title=What the doctor said|accessdate=27 July 2017|website=Lexis.pro}}</ref>, it has members from all the Spanish-speaking world.<ref name="about" />

This organization actively takes part in the organization of events relevant for the benefit of the linguistic aspects of the medical fields.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aptic.cat/es/jornadas-cientificas-y-profesionales-de-traduccion-medica/ |title=Scientific and Professional Meetings in Medical Translation |date=17 May 2012|publisher=APTIC}} {{es icon}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fundeu.es/noticia/jornadas-cientificas-y-profesionales-de-traduccion-medica-7289/ |title=Medical Translation |publisher=Fundéu|date=28 November 2012}} {{es icon}}</ref>
